-- JPMorgan Private Bank Appoints Andrew Cohen CEO of Asia Ultra-Rich Banking
-- Joyce Koh
-- 2010-06-17T06:14:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/jpmorgan-private-bank-appoints-andrew-cohen-ceo-of-asia-ultra-rich-banking.html

          
          
             JPMorgan Chase & Co.  said it
appointed  Andrew Cohen  as chief executive officer of private
banking for ultra-high net worth individuals in Asia-Pacific.  
 Cohen will be based in Hong Kong and report to Douglas
Wurth, CEO of JPMorgan’s private bank, according to an e-mailed
statement from the company. The executive, who previously headed
the JPMorgan’s South California wealth management business in
Los Angeles, will replace  Paul Scibetta , the bank said.  
